      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BROOKLYN (1) hit the ground running from out wide and was on speed early but swamped late when 6th at this track in a TG1-4W. Has ability and can bounce back. KIM GOT GAME (4) was safely held last time out, finishing fifth at this track over 342m behind Fine View (20.47) in a TG1-4W. Was in the money the start prior. Good beginner but will need a little luck from a middle draw. Has ability and is one of the better chances. TAZ MANIAC (2) has been settling off the speed lately, finishing sixth (20.85) last time in a Grade 6 at this track. Consistent performer from this draw with a win and eight minor placings to his credit. Has ability and can atone. SEBON STAR (5) comes into calculations after placing at this track and distance most recently.",
